{{for|the novel by R. A Salvatore|The Pirate King}} {{Infobox book | name = Pirate King | title_orig = | translator = | image = Pirate King (novel).jpg | caption = | author = [[Laurie R. King]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = [[Mary Russell (fictional)|Mary Russell]] | subject = | genre = [[Detective fiction]] | publisher = [[File:Flag of the United States.svg|25px|United States]] [[Bantam Press]] | release_date = 2011 | media_type = Print (hardback) | pages = 304 | isbn = 978-0-7490-4091-8 | dewey = | congress = PS3561.I4813 P57 2011 | oclc = | preceded_by = [[The God of the Hive]] | followed_by = [[Garment of Shadows]] }}
'''''Pirate King''''' is a 2011 mystery novel by American author [[Laurie R. King]]. Eleventh in the [[Mary Russell (fictional)|Mary Russell]] series, the story features married detectives Mary Russell and [[Sherlock Holmes]].
Sent to Lisbon and Morocco, where British studio Fflytte Films are creating a silent film version of ''[[The Pirates of Penzance]]'', undercover Mary Russell investigates a series of crimes targeting the production and confronts a high-stakes situation when actual pirates orchestrate a hostage situation.
==External links== * [http://www.laurierking.com/ Laurie R. King official website]
